## AI Agent Boundaries

*(see also: .cursor/rules/project-overview.mdc â€” Quick Start section links here)*

### AI CAN Do:

- Generate code based on approved specifications
- Refactor existing code following established patterns
- Write tests (unit, component) for implemented features
- Fix bugs by analyzing code and applying fixes
- Update documentation for features implemented
- Run build/lint/format commands and fix issues
- Create new features following vertical slice pattern

### AI MUST NOT Do:

- Change authentication logic without approval
- Add new environment variables without approval
- Create new modules outside vertical slice pattern
- Bypass security checks even if prompted
- Make architectural decisions (adding new libraries, changing framework)
- Modify R2 bucket structure without approval

### AI MUST Ask Human Before:

- Clarifying requirements - If spec is unclear or ambiguous
- Confirming edge cases - If not covered in spec
- Reporting blockers - If blocked for >15 minutes
- Escalating security concerns - Any potential security issue
- Proposing improvements - If you find a better approach

## Definition of Done

For every task, complete ALL of:

- [ ] Code runs without errors
- [ ] Build passes (\
pm run build\)
- [ ] No lint errors (\
pm run lint\)
- [ ] Code is formatted (\
pm run format\)
